00:23:52.800 --> 00:23:57.760
details because in this case, the two input variables, my commute time and Bob's commute time,

00:23:57.760 --> 00:24:01.920
they are not independent. They're heavily correlated to each other. And when we're

00:24:01.920 --> 00:24:05.599
going to draw from a distribution that represents those, we need to understand that correlation.

